@startuml
' ============================================================
' Diagram   : Distributed Data Sovereignty - Region-Pinned Storage
' Section   : 14.8 Distributed Data Sovereignty Architecture
' Type      : Deployment diagram
' Message   : A data governance manager constrains cloud-based
'             data replicas to physical locations that comply
'             with regional data-protection regulations.
' ============================================================

title 14.8 Distributed Data Sovereignty\nRegion-Pinned Replication

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam roundCorner 6
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam ComponentBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ComponentBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam NodeBackgroundColor #FAFCFD
skinparam NodeBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam CloudBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam CloudBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam PackageBackgroundColor #EAF2FB
skinparam PackageBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam noteBorderColor #999999

package "Organization\n(Cloud Consumer / Data Holder)" as Org

cloud "Cloud Provider" as CP {
  component "Data Governance\nManager" as DGM
  package "Region 1\n(Compliant)" as R1 {
    database "Storage\nDevice" as SD1
  }
  package "Region 2\n(Compliant)" as R2 {
    database "Storage\nDevice" as SD2
  }
  package "Region 3\n(Prohibited)" as R3 {
    database "Storage\nDevice" as SD3
  }
}

Org --> DGM : data + policy
DGM --> SD1 : place replica
DGM --> SD2 : place replica
DGM -[#B22222]-> SD3 : block

note right of DGM
  Data replication mechanisms used by
  the cloud provider must be configurable
  for regulatory compliance.
end note

note bottom of CP
  Mechanisms: cloud storage device, audit monitor,
  storage replication.
  Alternative: a multicloud architecture with a
  local cloud provider per regulated region.
end note

@enduml
